<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Insufficient Balance</title>
    <!-- Add Bootstrap CSS (make sure to include the correct path to your Bootstrap CSS file) -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="path/to/bootstrap.css">
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            text-align: center;
            background-color: #f7f7f7;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        .container {
            background-color: #fff;
            border-radius: 5px;
            padding: 20px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        h1 {
            color: #ff5733;
        }
        p {
            color: #333;
        }
        .instructions {
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin: 10px 0;
        }
        ol {
            color: #555;
        }
        li {
            color: #333;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Insufficient Balance in Your Wallet</h1>
        <p><strong>Please Add Money to Your Wallet</strong></p>

        <p><em>Important Information:</em><br>If you're seeing this message, it means there isn't enough balance in your wallet to complete your order using the wallet payment option. We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause. To proceed, you'll need to add money to your wallet.</p>

        <div class="instructions">
            <h2>How to Add Funds to Your Wallet:</h2>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Login to Your Account:</strong> Make sure you are logged into your account on our platform.</li>
                <li><strong>Access Your Wallet:</strong> Navigate to your account settings or profile, where you can find the 'Wallet' or 'Payment Options' section.</li>
                <li><strong>Add Funds:</strong> In the Wallet or Payment Options section, you will find an option to add funds. Click on it.</li>
                <li><strong>Enter Amount:</strong> You'll be prompted to enter the amount you want to add to your wallet. Please enter the desired amount.</li>
                <li><strong>Payment Method:</strong> Select your preferred payment method for adding funds. This can be a credit/debit card, bank transfer, or any other available payment method on our platform.</li>
                <li><strong>Confirm Transaction:</strong> Follow the on-screen instructions to confirm the transaction. You may need to provide necessary payment details.</li>
                <li><strong>Completion:</strong> Once the transaction is successfully completed, the funds will be added to your wallet.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <p>You can now proceed to place your order using the wallet payment option. The cost of your order will be deducted from your wallet balance.</p>

        <div class="instructions">
            <h2>Why Use Wallet Payment?</h2>
            <p>Using your wallet to make payments can be convenient and efficient. It eliminates the need to enter payment details for each order and allows for faster checkouts. Plus, it provides an overview of your transaction history and available balance.</p>
        </div>

        <p>If you have any questions or encounter issues while adding money to your wallet, please reach out to our customer support team for assistance. We're here to help you have a seamless experience with our platform.</p>

        <p>Thank you for choosing our services, and we appreciate your understanding and cooperation in maintaining your wallet balance.</p>
        
        <!-- Bootstrap Button for "Back to Home" -->
        <a href="/placeorder" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg"><h1>Back to Checkout</h1></a>

    </div>
    
    <!-- Add Bootstrap JS and jQuery (make sure to include the correct paths to your Bootstrap JS and jQuery files) -->
    <script src="path/to/jquery.js"></script>
    <script src="path/to/bootstrap.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
